value.title: US has assessed North Korea could be preparing to carry out first weapons test since Biden took office
value.excerpt: US intelligence has assessed that North Korea could be preparing to carry out their first weapons test since President Joe Biden came into office, according to several US officials speaking to CNN on condition of anonymity.

value.title: Biden says he supports bringing back the Senate's talking filibuster rule

value.title: Trump urges Americans to get Covid-19 vaccine: 'I would recommend it'
